tand der Modetheorie: Männer- und Frauenschuhe, hochmodische Accessoires und funktionale Fußbekleidungen, Vielfalt von Modellen und Mangel an Schuhen werden ebenso erörtert wie Materialinnovationen, Schuhdesign, Diskurse zur Fußgesundheit und nicht zuletzt die Wirtschaftsgeschichte der Schuhindustrie.  aShoes are much more than a functional and fashionable covering of the foot. As an integral part of material culture, they also highlight historical, social and cultural changes and schisms. With the use of themes such as foot health, material innovations and design, the contributions in this volume address the shoe as an object of fashion theory. Based on a research project on the shoes of the Swiss company Firma Bally, the volume deals with men and women's shoes, high fashion accessories and functional footwear, the lack of shoes, as well as the variety of models and the economic history of the shoe industry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aFootwear industryxHistory. 0aSchoemakerszSwitzerlandxHistoryy20th centuryvCongresses. 0aShoe industryzSwitzerlandxHistoryy20th centuryvCongresses. 0aShoeszSwitzerlandxDesignxHistoryy20th centuryvCongresses. 4aBally. 4aCultural Studies. 4aDesign. 4aGeschichte. 4aIndustrie. 4aKulturanthropologie. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aMaterial. 4aMedien. 4aMode. 4aWirtschaftsgeschichte. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aBally.  aCultural Anthropology.  aCultural History.  aCultural Studies.  aDesign.  aEconomic History.  aFashion Studies.  aHistory.  aIndustry.  aMaterial.  aMedia.1 aBreward, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBreyer, Nike U., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEhrenbold, Tobias, econtributor.4ctb4htt